<br>
Over in the Paladin forum, someone brought up about not having a full set of Ro to quest for - and perhaps if RO has not lesser armor than many unquestable sets - it would be a more quested after item.<br>
<br>
Here is what you get:<br>
BOOTS:  AC: +11 HP: +35<br>
BRACER: AC: +9 Magic Resist: +5 <br>
BREAST P: AC: +20 Str: +4 Fire Resist: +10 <br>
GAUNTLETS: AC: +12 Dex: +6 Poison Resist: +10<br>
GREAVES: AC: +13 Sta: +6 Cold Resist: +10<br>
HELM: AC: +13 Wis: +8 <br>
<br>
The resists are nice in this set - and would make an okay back-up suit of armor - but again, the super long faction work and travel is a little overboard (IMHO) for armor that will be replaced by time time you are in your 40's.<br>
<br>
So, since this is a fantasy game - I added some fantasy to my wish list:<br>
We are missing ARMS, BACK, WAIST, NECK & SHOULDERS here.<br>
<br>
We are a tank after all - and all this armor gives us only +4 STR.  In fact all the plusses are +4 STR, +8 Wis, +6 Dex  and +6 Sta.  My Shieldstorm gives me more than that in one item.  And it gives me +5 to all my resists too.<br>
<br>
So I suggest the following:<br>
ARMS: +10 AC, +5 Str, +3 AGI, +5 Cha<br>
SHOULDERS: +11 AC, +2 Dex, <br>
WAIST: +11 AC Effect Lightsource (blatantly stolen idea)<br>
NECK: +10 AC +10 INT +10 CHA (why Int?  Why not?  Paladins are supposed to be smart, even if we don't use that skill.<br>
BACK:  AC 11, +10 Cold, Effect Levitate.<br>
<br>
The Clincher to this is:  If all pieces are worn - then one can summon the SWORD OF RO.  Sword would have about the same stats as BABS - but with the effect GATE:  (But only to The Temple of Ro)<br>
Another effect is that the wearer of a full suit of Ro could change the Hue of their armor at will - to anything in the plate dying charts.<br>
All the additional pieces are about as un-uber as the originals.  <br>
I think it would be cool to rush into battle, changing my armor to a blood red or running to zone with mobs on my tail and changing armor to a bright YELLOW!! <p><CENTER>
